Date justification: strain GD01 (originally designated GZ01), isolated from the first autopsy sample of Guangdong. In particular, the first three SARS autopsies were performed in Guangzhou on 11, 12 and 25 February 2003 https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2435571/
Epi notes: We isolated the GD01 from a 54-year-old female patient. She was suspected being infected during her hospitalization by indirect contact with one of the “superspreaders”, who stayed in the same hospital as she did. She was one of the SARS cases with known transmission path connecting to the “Index Cases” identified in Guangdong Province. https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1672022903010143?via%3Dihub
Misc Notes: The viral isolate was from the autopsied lung tissue of the patient and propagated in Vero-E6 cell culture.
